<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 8:27PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Sherman,
eastern Dallam, northwestern Moore and northeastern Hartley Counties
through 915 PM CDT...
At 826 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 5 miles northeast of Conlen to 3 miles south of
Dalhart. Movement was southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Dumas, Dalhart, Stratford, Hartley, Cactus and Conlen.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
